      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "Slide 2: Introduction"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "There is a specific arithmetic applicable to pointers, which differs from the arithmetic used for integers or real numbers."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The operations that can be performed are:"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "• Addition"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "• Subtraction"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "• Comparison"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "• Assignment"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Pointers"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "2"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "Slide 3: Addition"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Adding an integer value x to a pointer variable means moving x positions forward in memory."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "To perform this displacement, we can also use the auto-increment operator (v++);"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Pointers"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "3"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "Slide 4: Subtraction"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Subtracting an integer value x from a pointer variable means moving x positions backward in memory."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The auto-decrement operator (v--) can also be used;"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Pointers"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "4"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "Slide 5: Comparison"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Comparing (==, !=) two pointers means evaluating the memory addresses they point to."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Pointers"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "5"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "Slide 6: Assignment"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Like other variable types, pointers can also be assigned (=) a value, which will normally be a memory address."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Pointers"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "6"
    },
    {
