    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "Slide 10: Variable Scope"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "In C, variables mainly act in two scopes:"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "• Local: Those whose lifetime ends when the \tfunction in which they were declared ends. Their use \tis restricted solely to that function."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "• Global: Those whose lifetime ends with the end of \tthe program. They are available in all functions that \tmake up that program."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Pointers"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "10"
    },
