    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "Slide 13: Parameter Passing"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "There are two ways to pass arguments to a function:"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "• By value: The value passed is a copy of the \toriginal. The original value is not modified."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "• By reference: The value passed is a pointer to the \tmemory address. The original value can be modified."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Pointers"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "13"
